WEBVTT

00:00.013 --> 00:02.248
<i>- Previously on</i> Good Witch.
- I've been hearing

00:02.273 --> 00:04.707
all of this talk
about some rare plant here.

00:04.743 --> 00:06.876
- The Middleton Merriwick.
- Malabathrum.

00:06.911 --> 00:09.045
For those days when nothing
seems to be going right.

00:09.080 --> 00:12.615
- Cassie, are you alright?
- Is something wrong?

00:12.651 --> 00:13.812
I don't know.

00:20.325 --> 00:23.092
The Merriwick looks like it's
trying to bloom, even though

00:23.128 --> 00:25.094
it must be hurting all
the way down to its roots.

00:25.130 --> 00:27.964
It's this whole town that's
hurting. Everyone was so excited

00:27.999 --> 00:30.533
to see this plant's flower; now
I don't know if we ever will!

00:30.568 --> 00:32.735
We're doing everything
we can to make it healthy.

00:32.771 --> 00:35.405
Yes, well, I need it to be
healthy now. I've already

00:35.440 --> 00:37.740
invited the tourism committee
to come here and see it

00:37.776 --> 00:39.976
so they'll put it
on the cover of their book!

00:40.011 --> 00:42.111
I decided that's what you would do.

00:42.147 --> 00:44.458
You know, believe in the best
and then, hope that it happens.

00:44.482 --> 00:46.746
- A solid course of action.
- Yes, but now

00:46.771 --> 00:48.418
I actually have to deliver, so...

00:48.453 --> 00:51.954
come on, Merriwick, don't let
this optimistic mayor down!

00:51.990 --> 00:54.157
Oh. I didn't realize you'd all be here.

00:54.192 --> 00:56.993
The Merriwick is the heart
and soul of our community.

00:57.028 --> 00:59.162
We all want to see it
back to full strength

00:59.197 --> 01:01.397
- as quickly as possible.
- That's right. She's one

01:01.433 --> 01:03.374
of our most prized possessions.

01:04.468 --> 01:06.350
It really is struggling.

01:07.305 --> 01:10.073
- What's in the soil?
- It's, uh...

01:10.108 --> 01:13.109
egg shells and coffee grounds.
I brought some things from Grey House.

01:13.144 --> 01:15.978
I'm using the best fertilizer I know of.

01:16.014 --> 01:18.081
Well, keep at it. I have
to get back to city hall

01:18.116 --> 01:20.294
and find out where Chief Sanders
is in his investigation.

01:20.318 --> 01:22.085
But in the meantime,

01:22.120 --> 01:25.421
stay strong. And believe!

01:33.244 --> 01:35.711
- Cassie!
- Hello, Sam!

01:35.746 --> 01:37.624
Trying to catch you since
I saw you on the corner.

01:37.648 --> 01:39.215
Well, I'm glad you finally did.

01:39.250 --> 01:41.395
I'm gonna grab a bite to eat
before I go to the hospital.

01:41.419 --> 01:43.319
- Are you hungry?
- Oh, I just ate.

01:43.354 --> 01:47.122
- Well, you could watch me eat.
- I can make time for that, yeah.

01:47.158 --> 01:52.228
Hey! Can we talk about
this little problem?

01:52.263 --> 01:54.730
Of course.

01:54.765 --> 01:57.299
I should probably
get back to work, then.

01:57.335 --> 01:59.268
Well, I can eat without an audience.

01:59.303 --> 02:01.237
- Hm! I'll see you around.
- Yeah.

02:07.411 --> 02:10.079
So this is the stuff
that made Ben's back

02:10.114 --> 02:11.925
- break out in hives.
- I still don't understand

02:11.949 --> 02:13.927
- how that could have happened.
- I know. I told him everything

02:13.951 --> 02:15.818
you've ever gave me worked amazing.

02:15.853 --> 02:18.065
Well, let's exchange that
for something that works now.

02:18.089 --> 02:20.267
Well, that's why you have the
best customer service in town.

02:20.291 --> 02:23.993
Hm...

02:25.630 --> 02:27.429
Uh...

02:30.067 --> 02:32.067
Here. Give him this.

02:32.103 --> 02:34.069
And this will help
with his sore muscles?

02:34.105 --> 02:36.272
Ask if it's something he'd like to try.

02:36.307 --> 02:38.974
- I will. Thanks.
- OK.

02:41.479 --> 02:45.314
- Abigail!
- Hey!

02:45.349 --> 02:48.250
- Hi!
- Ah, I'm completely

02:48.286 --> 02:51.020
out of vases at my store and
I thought maybe you had a few.

02:51.055 --> 02:53.289
- I do, except...
- I like this one.

02:53.324 --> 02:56.325
- Ooh...
- Oh...

02:56.360 --> 02:58.147
Whoops!

03:00.742 --> 03:02.364
Isn't that the Grey Lady?

03:02.400 --> 03:04.867
Slightly damaged, but yes.

03:04.902 --> 03:08.671
Well, I broke it, I'll fix it. And I'll
take as many of these as you can spare.

03:08.706 --> 03:10.673
Oh, except those vases are decorative

03:10.708 --> 03:13.709
for dry flowers, only.
They don't really hold water.

03:13.744 --> 03:18.113
- So you don't have what I need?
- Doesn't look like I do.

03:18.149 --> 03:21.717
- Hi.
- Grace. How was school?

03:21.752 --> 03:24.320
Horrible. There was
a pop quiz in calculus

03:24.355 --> 03:27.356
- that I did not see coming.
- Isn't that the point

03:27.391 --> 03:30.626
- of a pop quiz?
- Well, yeah,

03:30.661 --> 03:32.728
but usually I can tell
when they're about

03:32.763 --> 03:35.230
to happen and I always review,

03:35.266 --> 03:37.299
except this time, I didn't

03:37.335 --> 03:40.336
and if I failed that thing,
they might take me out of AP!

03:40.371 --> 03:42.571
They wouldn't do that
to a Merriwick girl.

03:42.607 --> 03:45.341
Except the Merriwick girls
don't seem to be operating

03:45.376 --> 03:46.836
at full Merriwick.

